This site reminds me of the Wall. It's like a Virtual Memorial site. I hope to see in this space someday stories from all sides. It is sad to note that Viets who died for the losing side have not been allowed to &quot;rest in peace&quot; and that veterans from the South and their families were systematically discriminated against for many years. There's no telling what sufferings their innocent children have had to endure.<br><br>
I look forward to the day when Viet Nam will have a &quot;Wall&quot; of its own to remember ALL her children who were sacrificed in the war. (Do you think Ms Maya Lin will be interested in working on such a project?)<br><br>
Thank you for this simple but powerful forum. And thanks to all who fought in VN. Your sacrifices are remembered and quietly appreciated in this man's heart. <br><br>
Ian
